name: MAIA
description: maia great or mother Maia is a name of the Roman and Greek mythology. In Greek mythology, Maia is the eldest of the seven Pleiades, the daughter of Pleione and Atlas and the mother of Hermes by Zeus. In Roman mythology, Maia was the mother of Mercury, who is equated with Hermes. Besides, Maia is a popular Maori name and a diminutive of the biblical name Maria.
